1071
01:03:35,646 --> 01:03:38,190
"and again to hastily don
our war gear

1072
01:03:38,357 --> 01:03:39,858
"while the monotonous patter
of the long roll

1073
01:03:40,025 --> 01:03:42,486
"summons to battle.

1074
01:03:42,653 --> 01:03:46,573
"Who knows, but again
the old flags, ragged and torn,

1075
01:03:46,740 --> 01:03:50,035
"snapping in the wind,
may face each other and flutter,

1076
01:03:50,202 --> 01:03:51,745
"pursuing and pursued,

1077
01:03:51,912 --> 01:03:55,249
"while the cries of victory
fill a summer day.

1078
01:03:55,415 --> 01:03:57,042
"And after the battle,

1079
01:03:57,209 --> 01:03:59,837
"then the slain and wounded
will arise

1080
01:04:00,003 --> 01:04:02,005
"and all meet together
under the two flags,

1081
01:04:02,172 --> 01:04:03,674
"all sound and well.

1082
01:04:03,841 --> 01:04:07,010
"There will be talking
and laughter and cheers,

1083
01:04:07,177 --> 01:04:10,681
"and all will say,
<i>did it not seem real?</i>

1084
01:04:10,848 --> 01:04:14,101
<i>Was it not
as in the old days?"</i>

